rge part from the colón free trade zone the largest free trade zone in the western hemisphere last year the zone accounted for  of panamas exports and  of its imports according to an analysis of figures from the colon zone management and estimates of panamas trade by the united nations economic commission for latin america and the caribbean panamas economy is also very much supported by the trade and export of coffee and other agricultural productscitation needed the bilateral investment treaty bit between the governments of the united states and panama was signed on october   the treaty protects us investment and assists panama in its efforts to develop its economy by creating conditions more favorable for us private investment and thereby strengthening the development of its private sector the bit was the first such treaty signed by the us in the western hemisphere a panama  united states trade promotion agreement tpa was signed in  approved by panama on july   and by us president obama on october   and the agreement entered into force on october   societyedit demographicsedit main article demographics of panama panamas population – panama recorded a population of  in its  census the proportion of the population aged below  in  was   of the population were aged between  and  with  of the population being  years or older more than half the population lives in the panama city–colón metropolitan corridor which spans several cities panamas urban population exceeds  making panamas population the most urbanized in central america ethnic groupsedit in  the population was  mestizo mixed white native american  native americans  black or african descent  mulatto and  white ethnic groups in panama include mestizo people who are a mix of european and native ancestry black or afropanamanians account for – of the population most afropanamanians live on the panamacolón metropolitan area the darien province la palma and bocas del toro neighborhoods in panama city that have large black populations include curundu el chorrillo rio abajo san joaquín el marañón san miguelito and santa anacitation needed black panamanians are descendants of african slaves brought to the americas on the atlantic slave trade the second wave of black people brought to panama came from the caribbean during the construction of the panama canal panama also has a considerable chinese and indian india population they were brought to work on the canal during its construction most chinesepanamanians reside in the province of chiriquícitation needed europeans and whitepanamanians are a minority in panama panama is also home to a small arab community that have mosques to practice islam the amerindian population includes seven ethnic groups the ngäbe kuna guna emberá buglé wounaan naso tjerdi teribe and bri bri languagesedit further information panamanian spanish spanish is the official and dominant language the spanish spoken in panama is known as panamanian spanish about  of the population speak spanish as their first language though many citizens who hold jobs at international levels or who are a part of business corporations speak both english and spanish native languages such as ngäbere are spoken throughout the country mostly in their native grounds over  panamanians hold their native languages and customs some new statistics show that as second language english is spoken by  french by  and arabic by citation needed largest citiesedit further information list of cities in panama panama city panamas capital these are the  largest panamanian cities and towns most of panamas largest cities are part of the panama city metropolitan area nº city population province  panama city  panamá  san miguelito  panamá  tocumen  panamá  david  chiriquí  las cumbres  panamá  colón  colón  la chorrera  west panamá  pacora  panamá  santiago de veraguas  veraguas  chitré  herrera religionedit main article religion in panama plaza de la independencia panama city the government of panama doe