also has a considerable chinese and indian india population they were brought to work on the canal during its construction most chinesepanamanians reside in the province of chiriquícitation needed europeans and whitepanamanians are a minority in panama panama is also home to a small arab community that have mosques to practice islam the amerindian population includes seven ethnic groups the ngäbe kuna guna emberá buglé wounaan naso tjerdi teribe and bri bri languagesedit further information panamanian spanish spanish is the official and dominant language the spanish spoken in panama is known as panamanian spanish about  of the population speak spanish as their first language though many citizens who hold jobs at international levels or who are a part of business corporations speak both english and spanish native languages such as ngäbere are spoken throughout the country mostly in their native grounds over  panamanians hold their native languages and customs some new statistics show that as second language english is spoken by  french by  and arabic by citation needed largest citiesedit further information list of cities in panama panama city panamas capital these are the  largest panamanian cities and towns most of panamas largest cities are part of the panama city metropolitan area nº city population province  panama city  panamá  san miguelito  panamá  tocumen  panamá  david  chiriquí  las cumbres  panamá  colón  colón  la chorrera  west panamá  pacora  panamá  santiago de veraguas  veraguas  chitré  herrera religionedit main article religion in panama plaza de la independencia panama city the government of panama does not collect statistics on the religious affiliation of citizens but various sources estimate that  to  of the population identifies itself as roman catholic and – as protestant the baháí faith community of panama is estimated at  of the national population or about  including about  of the guaymí population the church of jesus christ of latterday s